    "summary": "While cyberbullying shares many characteristics with traditional (offline) bullying (e.g., intention, aggressiveness, power imbalance, repetition), it can be particularly pernicious because of the medium in which it occurs. 3 As examples, a discrete incident of aggression that may have previously happened at a single time or place is not so constrained on the internet. 4 The abusive content itself can take the form of a comment, image, or recording. 5 And such aggressive content can be \"repeatedly viewed, shared, saved, commented on, or 'Liked' by others, and result in a cycle of repetitionand associated ongoing damage or trauma for a victim who re-lives the experience.\" 6Additionally, the lack of non-verbal cues make intention more difficult to discern, and the power imbalance that is oft"
